attachments.text: The repositories under my account at GitHub are all flagged as grey under the ‘Migrate’ option with a hover text of ‘Migration is now availble for this account’. When I first looked into the .org to .com migration I (mis)took this as a possibly temporary glitch but this is still the case. How do I get my (several dozen) repos from <http://travis-ci.org|travis-ci.org> to <http://travis-ci.com|travis-ci.com>? Is there really no ‘bulk’ or scripted option? I have found Travis CI to be a really useful tool and would prefer to use. Right it ...

text: Your account needs to be part of the beta to start migrating public repositories here. Please, sign up for the beta below. とも言われている。何で beta?
Migration is not available for this account と表示されるのだが、何でだろう。

Bram と協力して vim/vim を <http://travis-ci.com|travis-ci.com> に移行しようとしているが、上手くいっていない。
